  ('Goblet Squat Bottom Iso Hold', 'goblet-squat-bottom-iso-hold', 'Goblet Squat Bottom Iso Hold is an isometric exercise using the goblet-loaded squat bottom hold to develop hip, knee, ankle control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, NULL, 15, 75, 90, 'Loaded bottom-position squat hold that builds bracing, hip/knee/ankle range ownership, and position-specific strength.', 'Primary subrole: squat_knee_dominant_strength. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Loaded squat-bottom isometric', 'capacity', 'squat_knee_dominant_strength', 'goblet_squat_bottom_iso_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_flexion_isometric","knee_flexion_isometric","ankle_dorsiflexion_hold","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["quadriceps","glutes","adductors","spinal_erectors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["bottom_squat_ownership","loaded_breathing","foot_pressure"],"postural_shape":"goblet-loaded squat bottom hold","breathing_demand":"brace and breathe without collapsing","balance_demand":"stable bilateral stance","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the goblet-loaded squat bottom hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the goblet-loaded squat bottom hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, cable, bar, or body position as appropriate."