  ('Cossack Bottom Hold', 'cossack-bottom-hold', 'Cossack Bottom Hold is an isometric exercise using the deep Cossack bottom position to develop hip, knee, ankle control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 12, 50, 62, 'Deep lateral squat hold that builds adductor length-strength, hip control, and frontal-plane position tolerance.', 'Primary subrole: slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Frontal-plane hip and adductor isometric', 'resilience', 'slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience', 'cossack_bottom_frontal_plane_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_abduction_adduction_range_hold","knee_flexion_isometric","ankle_dorsiflexion_hold","trunk_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["adductors","glutes","quadriceps","hamstrings"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["frontal_plane_control","adductor_length_tension","foot_and_knee_alignment"],"postural_shape":"deep Cossack bottom position","breathing_demand":"slow breathing in controlled range","balance_demand":"moderate to high depending range","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the deep Cossack bottom position. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the deep Cossack bottom position.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, cable, bar, or body