  ('Hip Airplane Iso Hold', 'hip-airplane-iso-hold', 'Hip Airplane Iso Hold is an isometric exercise using the supported or unsupported single-leg hip airplane hold to develop hip, ankle, core control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 8, 45, 53, 'Single-leg hinge-and-rotation hold that teaches pelvis control, hip rotation ownership, and balance under low speed.', 'Primary subrole: balance_coordination_rhythm. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Single-leg hip rotation isometric', 'movement_intelligence', 'balance_coordination_rhythm', 'hip_airplane_balance_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_external_internal_rotation_control","hip_hinge_hold","ankle_balance_strategy","spine_anti_rotation"],"primary_tissues":["gluteus_medius","glutes","hamstrings","foot_intrinsics"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["single_leg_balance","pelvis_rotation_control","foot_tripod"],"postural_shape":"supported or unsupported single-leg hip airplane hold","breathing_demand":"quiet breathing while rotating pelvis without rushing","balance_demand":"high single-leg","coordination_demand":"high","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the supported or unsupported single-leg hip airplane hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the supported or unsupported single-leg hip airplane hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Bu