  ('Long-Lever Hamstring Bridge Iso Hold', 'long-lever-hamstring-bridge-iso-hold', 'Long-Lever Hamstring Bridge Iso Hold is an isometric exercise using the supine long-lever heel bridge hold to develop hamstrings, hip, core control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 10, 60, 70, 'Heel-supported long-lever bridge hold that builds hamstring capacity and posterior-chain control.', 'Primary subrole: slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Hamstring bridge isometric', 'resilience', 'slow_eccentric_isometric_joint_resilience', 'long_lever_hamstring_iso_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["knee_flexion_isometric_long_lever","hip_extension_isometric","pelvic_control","ankle_dorsiflexion_hold"],"primary_tissues":["hamstrings","glutes","calves","anterior_core"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["posterior_chain_tension","pelvis_level_control","hamstring_load_tolerance"],"postural_shape":"supine long-lever heel bridge hold","breathing_demand":"controlled breathing under hamstring tension","balance_demand":"stable supine","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the supine long-lever heel bridge hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the supine long-lever heel bridge hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, imp