  ('Hip Flexor March Iso Hold', 'hip-flexor-march-iso-hold', 'Hip Flexor March Iso Hold is an isometric exercise using the standing wall-supported march hold or supine march press to develop hip, core, spine control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 8, 25, 33, 'Standing or supine hip-flexion hold that activates hip flexors while reinforcing pelvic position.', 'Primary subrole: activate. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Hip-flexor activation isometric', 'prepare_and_access', 'activate', 'hip_flexor_march_activation_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_flexion_isometric","pelvic_control","knee_flexion_hold","spine_neutral_bracing"],"primary_tissues":["hip_flexors","anterior_core","quadriceps","glutes"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["march_position_ownership","pelvis_stack","opposite_side_glute_tension"],"postural_shape":"standing wall-supported march hold or supine march press","breathing_demand":"controlled breathing with ribs down","balance_demand":"moderate if standing","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the standing wall-supported march hold or supine march press. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the standing wall-supported march hold or supine march press.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, ca