  ('Wall Ankle Dorsiflexion Iso Press', 'wall-ankle-dorsiflexion-iso-press', 'Wall Ankle Dorsiflexion Iso Press is an isometric exercise using the half-kneeling or standing knee-to-wall press to develop ankle, foot, knee control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 10, 20, 30, 'Knee-to-wall pressure hold that creates usable dorsiflexion access while teaching foot tripod control.', 'Primary subrole: mobilize. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Ankle mobility-position isometric', 'prepare_and_access', 'mobilize', 'ankle_dorsiflexion_access_iso_press', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_dorsiflexion_isometric","knee_flexion_tracking","foot_pronation_supination_control","toe_extension_support"],"primary_tissues":["soleus","calves","achilles_tendon","foot_intrinsics"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["knee_over_toe_control","foot_tripod","active_range_ownership"],"postural_shape":"half-kneeling or standing knee-to-wall press","breathing_demand":"easy breathing while pressure is held","balance_demand":"stable split stance","coordination_demand":"low to moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the half-kneeling or standing knee-to-wall press. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the half-kneeling or standing knee-to-wall press.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implem