  ('Isometric Ankle Inversion Press', 'isometric-ankle-inversion-press', 'Isometric Ankle Inversion Press is an isometric exercise using the seated or standing ankle inward press against immovable surface to develop ankle, foot, calf control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 10, 25, 35, 'Controlled inward ankle pressure drill that builds medial ankle control and foot/ankle tissue tolerance.', 'Primary subrole: single_leg_balance_foot_ankle_hip_control. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Medial ankle isometric', 'resilience', 'single_leg_balance_foot_ankle_hip_control', 'ankle_inversion_iso_press', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_inversion_isometric","foot_arch_control","toe_pressure_control","knee_alignment_control"],"primary_tissues":["tibialis_posterior","foot_intrinsics","calves","medial_ankle_tissues"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["medial_ankle_pressure","arch_ownership","pain_free_force_direction"],"postural_shape":"seated or standing ankle inward press against immovable surface","breathing_demand":"normal breathing","balance_demand":"stable seated or supported stance","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the seated or standing ankle inward press against immovable surface. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the seated or standing ankle inward press against immovable surface.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the tar