  ('Foot Tripod Single-Leg Balance Hold', 'foot-tripod-single-leg-balance-hold', 'Foot Tripod Single-Leg Balance Hold is an isometric exercise using the barefoot or shoe-on single-leg stance hold to develop foot, ankle, hip control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 20, 30, 50, 'Single-leg stance hold that teaches foot tripod pressure, ankle strategy, knee tracking, and quiet hip control.', 'Primary subrole: balance_coordination_rhythm. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Foot and ankle balance isometric', 'movement_intelligence', 'balance_coordination_rhythm', 'foot_tripod_single_leg_balance_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_balance_strategy","hip_stability","knee_tracking","toe_pressure_control"],"primary_tissues":["foot_intrinsics","peroneals","tibialis_posterior","gluteus_medius"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["foot_tripod","single_leg_balance","quiet_knee_and_pelvis"],"postural_shape":"barefoot or shoe-on single-leg stance hold","breathing_demand":"normal breathing with eyes forward","balance_demand":"high single-leg static","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the barefoot or shoe-on single-leg stance hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the barefoot or shoe-on single-leg stance hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the