  ('Active Hang Scapular Hold', 'active-hang-scapular-hold', 'Active Hang Scapular Hold is an isometric exercise using the straight-arm active hang with shoulders packed to develop shoulder, forearm, elbow control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, NULL, 10, 60, 70, 'Straight-arm active hang that trains shoulder packing, grip, and scapular depression under bodyweight.', 'Primary subrole: scapular_wrist_hand_support_resilience. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Scapular depression hang isometric', 'resilience', 'scapular_wrist_hand_support_resilience', 'active_hang_scapular_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["scapular_depression_isometric","shoulder_flexion_overhead_support","elbow_extension_hold","grip_isometric"],"primary_tissues":["lats","lower_traps","rotator_cuff","forearm_flexors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["active_shoulder_pack","rib_control_in_hang","grip_with_open_breath"],"postural_shape":"straight-arm active hang with shoulders packed","breathing_demand":"steady breathing without rib flare","balance_demand":"suspended or assisted","coordination_demand":"moderate scapular awareness","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the straight-arm active hang with shoulders packed. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the straight-arm active hang with shoulders packed.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are alig