  ('Wall Handstand Hold', 'wall-handstand-hold', 'Wall Handstand Hold is an isometric exercise using the wall-supported handstand line hold to develop shoulder, wrist, core control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'INTERMEDIATE', 8, 3, NULL, 10, 75, 85, 'Wall-supported inverted hold that teaches body line, overhead shoulder support, and hand pressure.', 'Primary subrole: rotation_inversion_tumbling_foundations. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Inversion support isometric', 'movement_intelligence', 'rotation_inversion_tumbling_foundations', 'wall_handstand_line_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["shoulder_flexion_overhead_support","elbow_extension_lockout","wrist_extension_support","spine_line_control"],"primary_tissues":["deltoids","triceps","serratus_anterior","forearm_flexors","anterior_core"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["inverted_line","hand_pressure_balance","rib_pelvis_stack_overhead"],"postural_shape":"wall-supported handstand line hold","breathing_demand":"short calm breaths; no breath holding upside down","balance_demand":"high inverted support","coordination_demand":"high","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the wall-supported handstand line hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the wall-supported handstand line hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wa