  ('Overhead Dumbbell Hold', 'overhead-dumbbell-hold', 'Overhead Dumbbell Hold is an isometric exercise using the standing or half-kneeling overhead lockout hold to develop shoulder, wrist, core control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'INTERMEDIATE', 8, 3, NULL, 15, 75, 90, 'Locked-out overhead hold that builds shoulder stability, trunk stiffness, and load ownership above the head.', 'Primary subrole: upper_body_push_strength. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Loaded overhead support isometric', 'capacity', 'upper_body_push_strength', 'overhead_dumbbell_support_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["shoulder_flexion_overhead_lockout","elbow_extension_isometric","wrist_neutral_support","trunk_anti_extension"],"primary_tissues":["deltoids","triceps","rotator_cuff","serratus_anterior","anterior_core"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["overhead_lockout","rib_control_under_load","scapular_upward_rotation_support"],"postural_shape":"standing or half-kneeling overhead lockout hold","breathing_demand":"open-glottis breathing without rib flare","balance_demand":"moderate load/stance dependent","coordination_demand":"moderate","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the standing or half-kneeling overhead lockout hold. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the standing or half-kneeling overhead lockout hold.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are a