  ('Farmer Hold', 'farmer-hold', 'Farmer Hold is an isometric exercise using the standing tall with equal loads at sides to develop forearm, core, shoulder control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, NULL, 20, 90, 110, 'Two-hand heavy static hold that builds grip, posture, trunk stiffness, and whole-body loaded bracing.', 'Primary subrole: carry_trunk_loaded_bracing_strength. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Bilateral loaded grip and bracing hold', 'capacity', 'carry_trunk_loaded_bracing_strength', 'farmer_loaded_hold', '{"primary_joint_actions":["grip_isometric","shoulder_depression_hold","trunk_bracing","hip_stack_control"],"primary_tissues":["forearm_flexors","upper_traps","obliques","spinal_erectors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["loaded_posture","grip_under_load","even_shoulder_stack"],"postural_shape":"standing tall with equal loads at sides","breathing_demand":"controlled breathing while braced","balance_demand":"stable bilateral stance under load","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the standing tall with equal loads at sides. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the standing tall with equal loads at sides.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, band, cable, bar, or body position as appropriate.","Hold for about 20 s