  ('Isometric Mid-Thigh Pull', 'isometric-mid-thigh-pull', 'Isometric Mid-Thigh Pull is an isometric exercise using the mid-thigh pull against fixed pins or immovable bar to develop hip, knee, spine control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'ADVANCED', 8, 4, NULL, 4, 120, 124, 'High-intent fixed-bar pull from mid-thigh that trains force production at a specific athletic pull angle.', 'Primary subrole: tissue_capacity_isometric_eccentric_accessory. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'High-intent whole-body pull isometric', 'capacity', 'tissue_capacity_isometric_eccentric_accessory', 'mid_thigh_pull_overcoming_iso', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_extension_isometric","knee_extension_isometric","trunk_bracing","shoulder_extension_pull"],"primary_tissues":["glutes","hamstrings","quadriceps","spinal_erectors","upper_back"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["gradual_force_ramp","whole_body_pulling_intent","fixed_joint_angle_force"],"postural_shape":"mid-thigh pull against fixed pins or immovable bar","breathing_demand":"brace with controlled exhale; avoid sustained Valsalva","balance_demand":"stable bilateral stance","coordination_demand":"high intent with fixed position","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the mid-thigh pull against fixed pins or immovable bar. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the mid-thigh pull against fixed pins or immovable bar.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Creat