  ('Trap Bar Pin Pull Iso', 'trap-bar-pin-pull-iso', 'Trap Bar Pin Pull Iso is an isometric exercise using the trap bar set under fixed pins at chosen height to develop hip, knee, spine control, tissue tolerance, and force expression without visible joint movement.', 'ADVANCED', 8, 4, NULL, 5, 120, 125, 'Fixed-height trap-bar pull against pins that builds hinge force at a specific joint angle.', 'Primary subrole: hinge_posterior_chain_strength. Coach exact joint angles, gradual tension, steady breathing, and a clean stop. Isometrics are useful only when the athlete owns the position rather than surviving the clock.', 'Own the position, build steady pressure, breathe, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Overcoming hinge isometric', 'capacity', 'hinge_posterior_chain_strength', 'trap_bar_pin_pull_overcoming_iso', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip_extension_isometric","knee_extension_isometric","trunk_bracing","grip_isometric"],"primary_tissues":["glutes","hamstrings","quadriceps","spinal_erectors","forearm_flexors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":["fixed_height_pull","brace_before_force","foot_pressure"],"postural_shape":"trap bar set under fixed pins at chosen height","breathing_demand":"brace and controlled exhale; no prolonged breath hold","balance_demand":"stable bilateral stance","coordination_demand":"moderate to high","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Set up in the trap bar set under fixed pins at chosen height. Create tension gradually, hold the exact position, breathe under control, and end the set before posture, pain-free range, or breathing quality breaks.","setup":["Set the athlete in the trap bar set under fixed pins at chosen height.","Choose the easiest variation that allows pain-free alignment and calm breathing.","Coach a gradual build of tension instead of a sudden jerk into the position."],"execution_steps":["Create the target body shape and confirm the key joints are aligned.","Build pressure into the floor, implement, wall, ba